   "body" : "This is an alternative to #8364, and should fix #8079 without reintroducing the high-sigop attack fixed by #7081.\r\n\r\nWhen a transaction's sigops exceed (size * MAX_SIGOPS / MAX_SIZE), use that value as its size (for fee purposes and mempool sorting). This means that high-sigop transactions are no longer prevented, but they need to pay a fee corresponding to the maximally-used resource.",
